#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:25
msgid "Boot options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:26
msgid ""
"The ``k230`` machine supports K230 SDK boot through M-mode U-Boot, which "
"then starts OpenSBI/Linux with ``bootm``. It also supports direct Linux boot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:29
msgid ""
"K230 SDK Linux kernels use T-HEAD C9xx private MAEE page table attributes. "
"QEMU does not implement MAEE in the generic RISC-V MMU, so such kernels need "
"to be built with standard RISC-V PTE bits before they can boot under QEMU."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:34
msgid "Running"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:37
msgid "Direct Linux boot"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:39
msgid ""
"This flow lets QEMU load OpenSBI, Linux, initrd, and DTB directly, without "
"running SDK U-Boot. The Linux Image must be rebuilt with standard RISC-V PTE "
"bits before running under QEMU."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:43
msgid ""
"$ SDK=k230_sdk/output/k230_canmv_defconfig\n"
"$ qemu-system-riscv64 -machine k230 \\\n"
"   -kernel \"$SDK/images/little-core/Image\" \\\n"
"   -dtb \"/tmp/user-k230-qemu.dtb\" \\\n"
"   -initrd \"$SDK/images/little-core/rootfs.cpio.gz\" \\\n"
"   -append \"console=ttyS0,115200 earlycon=sbi cma=0\" \\\n"
"   -nographic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:53
msgid ""
"Direct boot uses the SDK little-core RAM layout for OpenSBI at "
"``0x08000000``, Linux at ``0x08200000``, and the DTB at ``0x0a000000``. The "
"initrd is placed by QEMU's generic RISC-V boot helper, and QEMU writes the "
"initrd range and kernel command line into ``/chosen``. The DTB passed with "
"``-dtb`` should be derived from ``$SDK/images/little-core/k230.dtb`` and "
"must describe that initrd location as usable memory and disable any devices "
"that are not emulated by this machine."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:62
msgid "U-Boot boot"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:64
msgid ""
"This flow starts SDK U-Boot in M-mode with ``-bios``. Until the SDK storage "
"path is modeled, place OpenSBI, Linux, initrd, and DTB in RAM with loader "
"devices and run ``bootm`` manually. The Linux Image must be rebuilt with "
"standard RISC-V PTE bits before running under QEMU."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:69
msgid ""
"$ SDK=k230_sdk/output/k230_canmv_defconfig\n"
"$ IMAGE=$SDK/images/little-core/Image\n"
"$ INITRD=$SDK/images/little-core/rootfs.cpio.gz\n"
"$ DTB=$SDK/images/little-core/k230.dtb\n"
"$ FWJUMP_UIMAGE=/tmp/k230-fw-jump.uImage\n"
"$ INITRD_END=$(printf \"0x%x\" $((0x0a100000 + $(stat -c %s \"$INITRD\"))))\n"
"$ \"$SDK/little/buildroot-ext/host/bin/mkimage\" \\\n"
"   -A riscv -O linux -T kernel -C none \\\n"
"   -a 0x8000000 -e 0x8000000 -n opensbi \\\n"
"   -d \"$SDK/images/little-core/fw_jump.bin\" \"$FWJUMP_UIMAGE\"\n"
"$ qemu-system-riscv64 -machine k230 \\\n"
"   -bios \"$SDK/little/uboot/u-boot\" \\\n"
"   -device loader,file=\"$FWJUMP_UIMAGE\",addr=0xc100000,force-raw=on \\\n"
"   -device loader,file=\"$IMAGE\",addr=0x8200000,force-raw=on \\\n"
"   -device loader,file=\"$INITRD\",addr=0xa100000,force-raw=on \\\n"
"   -device loader,file=\"$DTB\",addr=0xa000000,force-raw=on \\\n"
"   -nographic"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:89
msgid ""
"The loader addresses mirror the SDK ``k230_canmv_defconfig`` output. Read "
"the U-Boot addresses from the generated environment, and read the Linux RAM "
"base from the generated ``hw/k230.dts.txt``. This replaces the SDK storage "
"and decompression steps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:94
msgid "Press Enter to stop autoboot. At the U-Boot prompt, run these commands:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:96
msgid ""
"K230# setenv bootargs console=ttyS0,115200 earlycon=sbi cma=0\n"
"K230# fdt addr 0xa000000\n"
"K230# fdt resize 8192\n"
"K230# fdt set /chosen linux,initrd-start <0x0 0xa100000>\n"
"K230# fdt set /chosen linux,initrd-end <0x0 ${INITRD_END}>\n"
"K230# fdt set /soc/sdhci0@91580000 status disabled\n"
"K230# fdt set /soc/sdhci1@91581000 status disabled\n"
"K230# bootm 0xc100000 - 0xa000000"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../system/riscv/k230.rst:107
msgid ""
"Use ``setenv`` so ``bootm`` writes the kernel command line into ``/chosen/"
"bootargs``. The ``fdt`` commands select the loaded DTB, add space for edits, "
"describe the initrd range in ``/chosen``, and disable SDHCI nodes because "
"this machine does not emulate those controllers yet. Replace ``${INITRD_END}"
"`` with the host-calculated value above when typing the command. ``cma=0`` "
"avoids the SDK kernel reserving too much of the little-core memory window "
"for initramfs boot."
msgstr ""
